    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CROTON-ON-HUDSON: WHITE-SUPREMACY LITERATURE DISTRIBUTED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Corey Kilgannon</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Kilgannon, Corey</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Members of white-supremacist group World Church of the Creator distribute pamphlets in Croton-on-Hudson, NY, and say they will distribute thousands in Westchester County in membership drive (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Members of a group that said it placed pamphlets in Croton-on-Hudson say they will distribute thousands more in Westchester in a drive for members. ''We've begun a recruitment campaign around the entire New York area,'' said the Rev. Matt Hale, leader of the World Church of the Creator in East Peoria, Ill. The group advocates deporting Jews and immigrants who are not white. Several Croton residents reported getting a 32-page pamphlet, ''Facts That the Government and the Media Don't Want You to Know,'' about a week ago.</p>
        <p>Corey Kilgannon</p>
      </block>
